Program 2 — Working with Maven Project
Aim

To create, build, test, package, and run a Java application using Maven.

Step 1 — Create Maven Project

Open Command Prompt:

mkdir program2
cd program2

Create Maven project:

mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=myapp -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

Navigate project folder:

cd myapp
Step 2 — Configure pom.xml
pom.xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>myapp</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>

        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.13.2</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>

    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>

            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.22.2</version>

                <configuration>
                    <redirectTestOutputToFile>false</redirectTestOutputToFile>
                    <useSystemOut>true</useSystemOut>
                </configuration>

            </plugin>

        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>
Step 3 — Create App.java

Path:

src/main/java/com/example/App.java
package com.example;

public class App {

    public int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        App app = new App();

        int result = app.add(2, 3);

        System.out.println("2 + 3 = " + result);

        System.out.println("Application executed successfully!");
    }
}
Step 4 — Create AppTest.java

Path:

src/test/java/com/example/AppTest.java
package com.example;

import org.junit.Assert;
import org.junit.Test;

public class AppTest {

    @Test
    public void testAdd() {

        App app = new App();

        int result = app.add(2, 3);

        System.out.println("Running test: 2 + 3 = " + result);

        Assert.assertEquals(5, result);
    }
}
Step 5 — Compile Project
mvn compile

Observation:
Project compiled successfully.

Step 6 — Run Unit Tests
mvn test

Observation:
JUnit test executed successfully.

Step 7 — Package Project
mvn package

Observation:
JAR file generated inside target folder.

Step 8 — Run Application
java -cp target/myapp-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.example.App
Output
2 + 3 = 5
Application executed successfully!
